Now the error is very clear — your variables for the source image are empty, so the command is expanding to:

quay.io//:4.14.46-x86_64

👉 That means:

${PRODUCT_REPO} = ❌ empty

${RELEASE_NAME} = ❌ empty



---

🔥 Root cause

You didn’t export these two variables (or they got unset in this shell).


---

✅ Fix immediately

Run:

export PRODUCT_REPO="openshift-release-dev/ocp-release"
export RELEASE_NAME="release"


---

✅ Verify before running (important)

Check all variables:

echo ${PRODUCT_REPO}
echo ${RELEASE_NAME}
echo ${OCP_RELEASE}
echo ${ARCHITECTURE}

Expected:

openshift-release-dev/ocp-release
release
4.14.46
x86_64


---

✅ Then run mirror again

oc adm release mirror \
  -a ${LOCAL_SECRET_JSON} \
  --from=quay.io/${PRODUCT_REPO}/${RELEASE_NAME}:${OCP_RELEASE}-${ARCHITECTURE} \
  --to=${LOCAL_REGISTRY}/${LOCAL_REPOSITORY} \
  --to-release-image=${LOCAL_REGISTRY}/${LOCAL_REPOSITORY}:${OCP_RELEASE}-${ARCHITECTURE}


---

⚠️ About the warning

Flag --print-mirror-instructions's value 'icsp' has been deprecated

👉 Ignore this — it’s not your failure.
Just means newer OpenShift prefers IDMS instead of ICSP (you’re already using IDMS, so you're fine).


---

🧠 Why this caused your SNO outage

Because your earlier mirror likely:

❌ didn’t actually mirror anything (due to bad command)

or mirrored incomplete content


So the node:

tries to pull release image

fails → CRI-O fails → kubelet down → API EOF



---

🚀 After mirror completes

On SNO node:

systemctl restart crio
systemctl restart kubelet

Then check:

oc get nodes


